cation. An earlier draft of this toolkit became the basis for the UNDP/ United Nations Institute for Training and Research (UNITAR) e-learning course on the HDIA of Trade Policy. Positive feedback on the course contents received by nearly 100 participants of the first course (20 September - 22 October 2010) led to the publication and wider dissemination of the toolkit. This publication benefited from the editor, John Tessitore. Acknowledgements vi HUMAN DEVELOPMENT IMPACT ASSESSMENT OF TRADE POLICY: A Toolkit AAN ActionAid Nepal APTII Asia Pacific Trade and Investment Initiative ARV Antiretroviral ATC Agreement on Textiles and Clothing BTA Bilateral Trade Agreement CGE Computable General Equilibrium CPI Committee for Planning and Investment CSO Civil Society Organization DFQF Duty-Free and Quota-Free DTIS Diagnostic Trade Integrated Study EIC Economic Institute of Cambodia EPA Economic Partnership Agreement EU European Union GAMS General Algebraic Modelling System GATS General Agreement on Trade in Services GDI Gender Development Index GDP Gross Domestic Product GEM Gender Empowerment Measure GTAP Global Trade Analysis Project HDI Human Development Index HDIA Human Development Impact Assessment HDR Human Development Report HIV Human Immunodeficiency Virus IFPRI International Food Policy Research Institute ILO International Labour Organization IMF International Monetary Fund IPR Intellectual Property Right ITUC International Trade Union Confederation Lao PDR Lao People\u2019s Democratic Republic LDC Least Developed Country MDG Millennium Development Goal MFA Multifibre Arrangement MIMIC Multiple Indicators and Multiple Causes NAB National Advisory Board NGO Non-governmental Organization NRG National Reference Group NSC National Statistics Centre OECD Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development OHCHR Office of the High Commissioner for Human Rights OPHI Oxford Poverty and Human Development Initiative PRSP Poverty Reduction Strategy Papers RMG Ready-Made Garm