 they disseminated to both women and men in languages that they can understand? h Are actions to reduce the risks faced by women and vulnerable groups prioritized in disaster preparedness and response plans? h Is the importance of women as key change agents promoted and are women fully involved in community disaster manage- ment committees and disaster response drills? PRE-DISASTER: DISASTER RISK REDUCTION, MITIGATION AND PREPAREDNESS GENDER SMALL ISLAND DEVELOPING STATES DISASTER RISK MANAGEMENT CYCLE PROGRAM AND PROJECT MANAGEMENT CYCLE CHECKLISTS ADDITIONAL RESOURCES 34 Climate Risk Management \u2013 Policy h Is gender recognized in climate change discussions and research? h Do women participate in all decisions related to climate change at all levels? h Is there gender mainstreaming in all institutions dealing with climate change? h Is sex\u2013disaggregated data collected and published at every level wherever this is possible? h Are measureable gender\u2013related targets established and are practical tools that help integrate gender equality in climate protection created and applied? h Have gender\u2013sensitive indicators at national and local levels been developed, to be used in national communications and climate risk management projects? h Have outreach, capacity building, education and training been designed to take women into consideration? Do they enhance women\u2019s access to and participation in disaster risk reduction and climate change adaptation strategies and developmental activities? h Do adaptation and mitigation strategies support basic human security and the right to sustainable development?", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "dd907067-0834-4603-b0a8-d23c2cd45577": {"__data__": {"id_": "dd907067-0834-4603-b0a8-d23c2cd45577", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pa